# Whitelist approach: ignore everything, then un-ignore tooling files.
# This lets us have a Shopify theme in the same directory for testing
# without committing any theme code.

# Ignore everything
*

# Un-ignore the tooling
!.gitignore
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!install.sh
!LICENSE

# Skills (commands — legacy, kept until skills verified)
!.claude/
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/commands/*.md
!.claude/figma-best-practices.md

# Skills (new skills directory)
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/*/
!.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md
!.claude/skills/*/gotchas.md
!.claude/skills/*/reference/
!.claude/skills/*/reference/*.md

# Docs
!docs/
!docs/**

# Theme profiles (pre-loaded knowledge, committed)
!.claude/figma-sync/
!.claude/figma-sync/theme-profiles/
!.claude/figma-sync/theme-profiles/*.json
!.claude/figma-sync/theme-profiles/README.md

# Always ignore runtime state (generated per project)
.claude/figma-sync/theme-profiles/manifest.json
